A skeleton of a modern Carbon QuickTime application. QTCarbonShell is a simple QuickTime player framework demonstrating how to incorporate QuickTime Movie support into a Carbon application. The sample demonstrates playback, editing and saving of QuickTime Movies. It is NIB-based for user-interface elements and uses the Carbon Movie Controller.\
\
This sample supersedes the older Macintosh QTShell and qtshellCEvents samples.\
