\f1\b \cf0 NOTE
\f2\b0 :\
\
While the Carbon Movie Control is available on both Mac OS X 10.3.x w/ QuickTime 6.x or QuickTime 7 and Mac OS X 10.4+ w/QuickTime 7, if you're specifically targeting a Carbon QuickTime application for 10.4 or greater the preferred control for Movie playback is HIMovieView.\
\
HIMovieView is more robust, uses Core Video and OpenGL internally to render Movies and will be supported moving forward.\
\
HIMovieView however, is not available on Mac OS X 10.3.x even with the latest version of QuickTime installed. Therefore using both depending on the situation is quite valid. See TN2140 for a full description of the Carbon Movie Control.\
\

